MAIN IDEA IN SIMPLE ENGLISH

At every index:

Current total sum is known.

Now ask:

Did some old prefix exist which I can remove so remaining becomes k?

If yes:

subarray found
Why HashMap?

Because we need to quickly know:

Have we seen this old prefix before?

HashMap gives instant lookup.

MOST IMPORTANT LINE
count += map.get(sum-k);

Meaning:

How many old prefixes exist that can be removed
to make remaining sum = k?
ONE FINAL VISUAL

Suppose:

currentSum = 10
k = 4

Ask:

What old prefix should exist?
10 - oldPrefix = 4

So:

oldPrefix = 6

If prefix sum 6 existed earlier:

10 - 6 = 4

So middle subarray sum is 4.

okay code
import java.util.*;

class Solution {
    public int subarraySum(int[] nums, int k) {

        // Stores: prefixSum -> frequency
        HashMap<Integer, Integer> map = new HashMap<>();

        // Prefix sum 0 exists once initially
        map.put(0, 1);

        int sum = 0;
        int count = 0;

        for(int num : nums) {

            // Current prefix sum
            sum += num;

            // Check if old prefix exists
            // such that:
            // currentSum - oldPrefix = k
            // oldPrefix = currentSum - k
            if(map.containsKey(sum - k)) {

                count += map.get(sum - k);
            }

            // Store current prefix sum
            map.put(sum, map.getOrDefault(sum, 0) + 1);
        }

        return count;
    }
}
